{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "intro_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# SMS Spam Prediction and Detailed Model Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook loads the fine-tuned **BERT (bert-base-uncased)** classifier, runs predictions on single text samples, and performs a comprehensive evaluation on the held-out test split of the **SMS Spam Collection dataset**.\n",
    "\n",
    "> [!NOTE]\n",
    "> **Directory Assumption**: This notebook is designed to be executed with the working directory set to `model/` (the directory where this file resides)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "imports_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Import Libraries\n",
    "We start by importing the necessary PyTorch and Hugging Face Transformers libraries."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "ae7d3739",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "from transformers import BertTokenizer, BertForSequenceClassification"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "path_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Define Model Path\n",
    "Specify the path where our fine-tuned BERT model checkpoints are saved using `pathlib.Path` relative resolution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "e43f448a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Saved Model Path: saved_model\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "save_path = Path(\"saved_model\")\n",
    "print(\"Saved Model Path:\", save_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "missing_weights_warning_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### ⚠️ Missing Model Weights Warning\n",
    "\n",
    "* **`model/saved_model/model.safetensors`** contains the fine-tuned BERT model weights (~438 MB).\n",
    "* This file is **intentionally excluded** from normal Git tracking because it exceeds GitHub's standard 100 MB per-file tracking limit.\n",
    "* Prediction **requires** the fine-tuned model weights. The file `model.safetensors` must exist inside `model/saved_model/` before running the cell below.\n",
    "* If you are running this after cloning, you must either train the model locally (`train.ipynb`) or obtain and place the fine-tuned weights file into the `saved_model/` directory first. The trained weights are not currently hosted on a public repository."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "load_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Load Tokenizer and Fine-tuned Model\n",
    "We load the tokenizer directly from `bert-base-uncased` to prevent JSON loading issues, and load the fine-tuned weights from the local `saved_model` directory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "ddfe4257",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "BERT Tokenizer and Fine-Tuned Spam Model loaded successfully!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "tokenizer = BertTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"bert-base-uncased\")\n",
    "model = BertForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(save_path)\n",
    "print(\"BERT Tokenizer and Fine-Tuned Spam Model loaded successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "device_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4. Device Setup\n",
    "Configure device tracking to run model operations on the GPU (CUDA) if available, or fall back to the CPU."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "19f0857d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Using device: cpu\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n",
    "model.to(device)\n",
    "model.eval()\n",
    "print(\"Using device:\", device)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "predict_func_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5. Define Prediction Function\n",
    "Create a function that processes an input string, tokenizes it, performs inference with the fine-tuned BERT model, and returns the predicted label and confidence score."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "a6d764ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def predict_spam(message):\n",
    "    encoding = tokenizer(\n",
    "        message,\n",
    "        truncation=True,\n",
    "        padding=True,\n",
    "        max_length=128,\n",
    "        return_tensors=\"pt\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Move inputs to the configured device\n",
    "    encoding = {\n",
    "        key: value.to(device)\n",
    "        for key, value in encoding.items()\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        outputs = model(**encoding)\n",
    "\n",
    "    probabilities = torch.softmax(outputs.logits, dim=1)\n",
    "    predicted_class = torch.argmax(probabilities, dim=1).item()\n",
    "    confidence = probabilities[0][predicted_class].item() * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "    if predicted_class == 1:\n",
    "        prediction = \"SPAM\"\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        prediction = \"HAM\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"Prediction:\", prediction)\n",
    "    print(f\"Confidence: {confidence:.2f}%\")\n",
    "    return prediction, confidence"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "test_single_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6. Test Single Messages\n",
    "Let's test the prediction function on two sample messages (one obvious spam and one typical ham)."
   ]
  },
  {
