   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eval_header_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Detailed Model Evaluation on Test Split\n",
    "\n",
    "Below, we perform a detailed evaluation of our saved fine-tuned model by loading the dataset, reconstructing the exact train/test split, generating predictions on the test set, and printing the **Confusion Matrix** and **Classification Report**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eval_imports_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 9. Import Evaluation Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "f0be5c09",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, classification_report"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eval_load_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 10. Load and Preprocess Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "662a753a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "   label                                               text\n",
      "0      0  Go until jurong point, crazy.. Available only ...\n",
      "1      0                      Ok lar... Joking wif u oni...\n",
      "2      1  Free entry in 2 a wkly comp to win FA Cup fina...\n",
      "3      0  U dun say so early hor... U c already then say...\n",
      "4      0  Nah I don't think he goes to usf, he lives aro...\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dataset_path = Path(\"../dataset/spam.csv\")\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(\n",
    "    dataset_path,\n",
    "    encoding=\"ISO-8859-1\"\n")\n",
    "df = df[[\"v1\", \"v2\"]]\n",
    "df.columns = [\"label\", \"text\"]\n",
    "df[\"label\"] = df[\"label\"].map({\n",
    "    \"ham\": 0,\n",
    "    \"spam\": 1\n",
    "})\n",
    "print(df.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eval_split_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 11. Reconstruct Split\n",
    "We use the exact split parameters used in the training script (`test_size=0.2`, `random_state=42`) to obtain the correct held-out test data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "eb6386fc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Testing Samples: 1115\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "train_texts, test_texts, train_labels, test_labels = train_test_split(\n",
    "    df[\"text\"].tolist(),\n",
    "    df[\"label\"].tolist(),\n",
    "    test_size=0.2,\n",
    "    random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(\"Testing Samples:\", len(test_texts))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eval_token_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 12. Tokenize Test Split"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "d62fc24e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "test_encodings = tokenizer(\n",
    "    test_texts,\n",
    "    truncation=True,\n",
    "    padding=True,\n",
    "    max_length=128\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eval_dataset_class_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 13. Create Dataset Class for Evaluation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "0e085fa4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class SpamTestDataset(torch.utils.data.Dataset):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, encodings, labels):\n",
    "        self.encodings = encodings\n",
    "        self.labels = labels\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __getitem__(self, index):\n",
    "        item = {\n",
    "            key: torch.tensor(value[index])\n",
    "            for key, value in self.encodings.items()\n",
    "        }\n",
    "        item[\"labels\"] = torch.tensor(self.labels[index])\n",
    "        return item\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __len__(self):\n",
    "        return len(self.labels)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eval_inference_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 14. Batch Inference\n",
    "Instantiate `test_dataset` and feed batch data into the DataLoader. We loop through the DataLoader on the selected device and collect our predictions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "6577bf80",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Predictions generated successfully!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "test_dataset = SpamTestDataset(test_encodings, test_labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "test_loader = DataLoader(\n",
    "    test_dataset,\n",
    "    batch_size=8\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "predicted_labels = []\n",
    "model.eval()\n",
    "\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    for batch in test_loader:\n",
    "        input_ids = batch[\"input_ids\"].to(device)\n",
    "        attention_mask = batch[\"attention_mask\"].to(device)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        outputs = model(\n",
    "            input_ids=input_ids,\n",
    "            attention_mask=attention_mask\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \n",
    "        predictions = torch.argmax(\n",
    "            outputs.logits,\n",
    "            dim=1\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        predicted_labels.extend(\n",
    "            predictions.cpu().numpy()\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Predictions generated successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eval_metrics_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 15. Generate Metrics Output\n",
    "Compute and print evaluation accuracy, confusion matrix, and full classification report."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "739567d6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Verified Test Accuracy: 99.37%\n",
      "\n",
      "Confusion Matrix:\n",
      "[[963   2]\n",
      " [  5 145]]\n",
      "\n",
      "Classification Report:\n",
      "              precision    recall  f1-score   support\n",
      "\n",
      "         HAM       0.99      1.00      1.00       965\n",
      "        SPAM       0.99      0.97      0.98       150\n",
      "\n",
      "    accuracy                           0.99      1115\n",
      "   macro avg       0.99      0.98      0.99      1115\n",
      "weighted avg       0.99      0.99      0.99      1115\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cm = confusion_matrix(test_labels, predicted_labels)\n",
    "report = classification_report(test_labels, predicted_labels, target_names=[\"HAM\", \"SPAM\"])\n",
    "acc = accuracy_score(test_labels, predicted_labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Verified Test Accuracy: {acc * 100:.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nConfusion Matrix:\")\n",
    "print(cm)\n",
    "print(\"\\nClassification Report:\")\n",
    "print(report)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "limitations_md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 16. Known Model Limitations\n",
    "While the model achieves a high **99.37%** validation accuracy on the held-out split of the **SMS Spam Collection dataset**, it is important to understand its constraints when used in real-world environments:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Dataset Bias (SMS vs. Email)**: The model is trained on a dataset representing SMS messages from the late 2000s/early 2010s. Modern formal emails or rich-text promotional messages differ significantly in length, formatting, and vocabularies.\n",
    "2. **False Positives (Domain Mismatch)**: A formal recruitment or onboarding email (e.g. inviting a user to a WhatsApp group) may trigger spam classification because it contains common call-to-action phrases like \"Click on the Link\" or \"JOIN GROUP\".\n",
    "3. **Text-Only Context**: The model classifies *strictly* based on text patterns. It lacks context about:\n",
    "   - Sender identity / sender email domain reputation\n",
    "   - URL reputation checks\n",
    "   - Domain-level authentication (SPF, DKIM, DMARC)\n",
    "   - User registration status or previous conversation history\n",
    "   \n",
    "These limitations should be taken into account when moving from prototyping to production."
   ]
  }
 ],
